%N A398019 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} theta(k) * log(k) / k^2, where theta(k) is the number of unitary divisors of k (A034444).
%H A398019 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 382, Corollary 2.10.
%F A398019 Equals 60*log(A) + 600*log(A_3), where A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962), and A_3 is the third Bendersky constant (A243263).
%F A398019 Note that Sum_{k>=1} theta(k) / k^2 = 5/2.
